# Worktree Isolation

- Never edit host checkout files for implementation work.
- Start each task in an isolated git worktree: `git worktree add -b <branch-name> .worktrees/<task-name> main`
- Always branch from `main` (the default branch for ARO-RP).
- Keep host checkout read-only — use it only for exploration, review, and context.
- Only include task-related files in commits.

## Before Starting

1. Run `gh pr list --state open` to check for parallel work that may conflict.
2. Create the worktree from the host checkout root.
3. Verify ancestry: `git merge-base --is-ancestor main HEAD`

## Branch Naming (Non-Blocking)

- Preferred branch format: `<github-alias>/<jira-id>/<short-description>`.
- Example: `tuxerrante/aro-1234/feature-description`.
- This is a non-blocking quality gate: follow when possible, but do not stop work if an existing branch name differs.

## Implementation

- All edits, builds, and tests happen inside the worktree directory.
- Never `cd` back to host checkout to make changes.
